{"query": {"redirects": [{"to": "John Goldthorpe", "from": "John H. Goldthorpe"}], "pages": {"877062": {"lastrevid": 638779735, "pageid": 877062, "canonicalurl": "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/John_Goldthorpe", "title": "John Goldthorpe", "editurl": "http://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=John_Goldthorpe&action=edit", "length": 4835, "contentmodel": "wikitext", "pagelanguage": "en", "touched": "2015-03-30T12:13:44Z", "ns": 0, "fullurl": "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/John_Goldthorpe", "revisions": [{"*": "<p><b>John Harry Goldthorpe</b> <a href=\"/wiki/Fellow_of_the_British_Academy\" title=\"Fellow of the British Academy\" class=\"mw-redirect\">FBA</a> (born 27 May 1935) is a <a href=\"/wiki/United_Kingdom\" title=\"United Kingdom\">British</a> <a href=\"/wiki/Sociologist\" title=\"Sociologist\" class=\"mw-redirect\">sociologist</a> working at the <a href=\"/wiki/Department_of_Social_Policy_and_Intervention,_University_of_Oxford\" title=\"Department of Social Policy and Intervention, University of Oxford\">Department of Social Policy and Intervention, University of Oxford</a> as well as being an emeritus Fellow of <a href=\"/wiki/Nuffield_College,_Oxford\" title=\"Nuffield College, Oxford\">Nuffield College</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Oxford_University\" title=\"Oxford University\" class=\"mw-redirect\">Oxford</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\"><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup> He works in the areas of <a href=\"/wiki/Social_stratification\" title=\"Social stratification\">social stratification</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Macrosociology\" title=\"Macrosociology\">macrosociology</a>, and recently cultural consumption. He has made important contributions to the practical application of sociological <a href=\"/wiki/Rational_Choice_Theory\" title=\"Rational Choice Theory\" class=\"mw-redirect\">Rational Choice Theory</a>. He was editor of <i><a href=\"/wiki/Sociology_(journal)\" title=\"Sociology (journal)\">Sociology</a></i> 1970-1973.\n</p><p>He was a student of <a href=\"/wiki/David_Glass_(sociologist)\" title=\"David Glass (sociologist)\">David Glass</a> at the <a href=\"/wiki/London_School_of_Economics\" title=\"London School of Economics\">London School of Economics</a>.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div id=\"toctitle\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Early_life\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Early life</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Research\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Research</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Works\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Works</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Early_life\">Early life</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=John_Goldthorpe&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Early life\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Goldthorpe was born in <a href=\"/wiki/Great_Houghton,_South_Yorkshire\" title=\"Great Houghton, South Yorkshire\">Great Houghton</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/West_Riding_of_Yorkshire\" title=\"West Riding of Yorkshire\">West Riding of Yorkshire</a>; his father was a colliery clerk. He was educated at \nWath-upon-Dearne Grammar School, <a href=\"/wiki/University_College,_London\" title=\"University College, London\" class=\"mw-redirect\">University College, London</a> and the <a href=\"/wiki/London_School_of_Economics\" title=\"London School of Economics\">London School of Economics</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Goodhart2009_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Goodhart2009-2\"><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Research\">Research</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=John_Goldthorpe&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Research\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>His work on social class led to the well-established <a href=\"/wiki/Class_stratification#Class_Schema\" title=\"Class stratification\">Goldthorpe class schema</a>, one of the standard approaches to classify class in sociology. The Goldthorpe class schema is based on eleven classes, which are grouped into three main clusters\u2014the <a href=\"/wiki/Service_class\" title=\"Service class\" class=\"mw-redirect\">service class</a> (or salariat), the intermediate class, and the working class.\n</p><p>Goldthorpe has contributed to the understanding of <a href=\"/wiki/Social_mobility\" title=\"Social mobility\">social mobility</a>. Goldthorpe is also well known for his work on the <a href=\"/wiki/Embourgeoisement_thesis\" title=\"Embourgeoisement thesis\">embourgeoisement thesis</a> which he dispelled in 1963.\n</p><p>He is also known for his vocal critiques of the concepts of 'cultural capital' and 'habitus', as initially formulated by <a href=\"/wiki/Pierre_Bourdieu\" title=\"Pierre Bourdieu\">Pierre Bourdieu</a>, which Goldthorpe argues are ill informed, both empirically and theoretically.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\"><span>[</span>3<span>]</span></a></sup>\n</p><p>He was elected a Fellow of the <a href=\"/wiki/British_Academy\" title=\"British Academy\">British Academy</a> in 1984. He is also a foreign member of the <a href=\"/wiki/Royal_Swedish_Academy_of_Sciences\" title=\"Royal Swedish Academy of Sciences\">Royal Swedish Academy of Sciences</a> since 2001.<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\"><span>[</span>4<span>]</span></a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Works\">Works</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=John_Goldthorpe&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Works\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li>2007 <i>On Sociology (2nd Edition)</i>. Stanford: Stanford University Press.</li>\n<li>2004 <i>The economic basis of social class</i>. London: Centre for Analysis of Social Exclusion, <a href=\"/wiki/London_School_of_Economics\" title=\"London School of Economics\">London School of Economics</a>.</li>\n<li>2000 <i>On sociology: numbers, narratives, and the integration of research and theory</i>. Oxford: Oxford University Press. <a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/0198295715\" class=\"internal mw-magiclink-isbn\">ISBN 0-19-829571-5</a></li>\n<li>1996 <i>Rational choice theory and large-scale data analysis</i>. Oxford: Oxford University Press.</li>\n<li>1992 <i>The constant flux: a study of class mobility in industrial societies</i>. Oxford: Clarendon Press. <a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/0198273835\" class=\"internal mw-magiclink-isbn\">ISBN 0-19-827383-5</a></li>\n<li>1992 <i>Revised class schema</i>. London: Social and Community Planning Research.</li>\n<li>1991 <i>The uses of history in sociology: reflections on some recent tendencies</i>. Oxford: Nuffield College.</li>\n<li>1987 <i>Social mobility and class structure in modern Britain</i>. Oxford: Clarendon Press. <a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/0198272863\" class=\"internal mw-magiclink-isbn\">ISBN 0-19-827286-3</a></li>\n<li>1963 <i>The affluent worker: political attitudes and behaviour</i>. Cambridge: Cambridge University Press. <a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/0521072042\" class=\"internal mw-magiclink-isbn\">ISBN 0-521-07204-2</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=John_Goldthorpe&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external free\" href=\"http://www.nuffield.ox.ac.uk/sociology/Group/goldthorpe.html\">http://www.nuffield.ox.ac.uk/sociology/Group/goldthorpe.html</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Goodhart2009-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-Goodhart2009_2-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><span class=\"citation news\">Goodhart, David (July 26, 2009). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.timesonline.co.uk/tol/news/politics/article6727099.ece\">\"They\u2019re wrong \u2013 social mobility is not going downhill\"</a>. <i>The Sunday Times</i>.</span><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AJohn+Goldthorpe&amp;rft.atitle=They%E2%80%99re+wrong+%E2%80%93+social+mobility+is+not+going+downhill&amp;rft.aufirst=David&amp;rft.au=Goodhart%2C+David&amp;rft.aulast=Goodhart&amp;rft.date=July+26%2C+2009&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.timesonline.co.uk%2Ftol%2Fnews%2Fpolitics%2Farticle6727099.ece&amp;rft.jtitle=The+Sunday+Times&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><span class=\"citation web\">John H. Goldthorpe (February 2007). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.sociologia.uniroma1.it/USERS/salmieri/sociologia%20della%20cultura%20e%20sociologia%20dei%20processi%20culturali%202011-2012/10_Pierre_Bourdieu_la_pratica_della_cultura/Cultural_Capital_Some_Critical_observations.pdf\">\"<span style=\"padding-left:0.2em;\">\"</span>Cultural Capital\": Some Critical Observations\"</a>. <i>Sociologica (Italian Journal of Sociology on line)</i>. <a href=\"/wiki/Digital_object_identifier\" title=\"Digital object identifier\">doi</a>:<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//dx.doi.org/10.2383%2F24755\">10.2383/24755</a>.</span><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AJohn+Goldthorpe&amp;rft.atitle=%22Cultural+Capital%22%3A+Some+Critical+Observations&amp;rft.au=John+H.+Goldthorpe&amp;rft.aulast=John+H.+Goldthorpe&amp;rft.date=February+2007&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.sociologia.uniroma1.it%2FUSERS%2Fsalmieri%2Fsociologia%2520della%2520cultura%2520e%2520sociologia%2520dei%2520processi%2520culturali%25202011-2012%2F10_Pierre_Bourdieu_la_pratica_della_cultura%2FCultural_Capital_Some_Critical_observations.pdf&amp;rft_id=info%3Adoi%2F10.2383%2F24755&amp;rft.jtitle=Sociologica+%28Italian+Journal+of+Sociology+on+line%29&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><span class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.kva.se/KVA_Root/eng/contact/searchcontacts/detail.asp?PersonID=4067\">\"The Royal Swedish Academy of Sciences: John H. Goldthorpe\"</a><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2009-05-01</span></span>.</span><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AJohn+Goldthorpe&amp;rft.btitle=The+Royal+Swedish+Academy+of+Sciences%3A+John+H.+Goldthorpe&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.kva.se%2FKVA_Root%2Feng%2Fcontact%2Fsearchcontacts%2Fdetail.asp%3FPersonID%3D4067&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook\" class=\"Z39